8 Subject: Consumer protection; weights and measures; dynamic pricing
9 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to establish a
10 moratorium on the use of electronic shelf labels or dynamic pricing by retailers
11 selling consumer commodities in the State. The moratorium would be
12 effective until January 15, 2027. During the moratorium, the bill would
13 require the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets to report to the General
14 Assembly regarding the use of electronic shelf labels or dynamic pricing and
15 how to protect consumers. When the moratorium expires, provisions regarding
16 the use of electronic shelf labels or dynamic pricing would go into effect.
