9 Sec. 2. 6 V.S.A. § 684 is added to read:
10 § 684. USE OF ELECTRONIC SHELF LABELS; DYNAMIC PRICING
11 (a) A retailer selling a consumer commodity in the State may use electronic
12 shelf labels to disclose to consumers the retail price and unit price of the
13 consumer commodity for sale.
14 (b) A retailer using electronic shelf labels shall not use dynamic pricing to
15 alter the retail price or unit price of a consumer commodity while the retailer is
16 open to the public.
17 (c) A retailer shall not alter the retail price or unit price of a consumer
18 commodity until at least 24 hours since the last alteration to the retail price or
19 unit price for the consumer commodity.
